Sentencing hearing proceeded. Statements made as to sentencing. Additional statements made by Darlene J.

As to COUNT 2-
Court ordered defendant to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Correction; credit for 2 days time served.

Court STAYED the sentence on COUNT 2 and placed defendant on probation for 14 MONTHS with the following conditions:

1) Attend a Batterer's Intervention program;
2) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges (including the Domestic Abuse Assessment) during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
3) Court ordered the defendant to provide a DNA sample. Court WAIVED DNA surcharge due to the length of time between this case and the defendant's last conviction;
4) Commit no new crimes rising to the level of probable cause;
5) Defendant may continue having contact with minor children;
6) No violent contact with the victim Darlene J.;

Per Court, cash bail on deposit to apply towards costs, fees and surcharges.
Court vacated the jury trial date of 9/15/15.

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Memorandum of Conditions of Probation;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief. Probation Review Hearing scheduled for October 23, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
